passages.text: August 29, 2025 07:44 AM GMT
Australian mortgages grew at an annualised pace of \(\sim 6\%\) SAAR in July, broadly in line with the average pace since the start of 2025.
Major bank mortgage growth averaged \(\sim 3\%\) in July (ANZ: \(+2.1\%\) ; CBA: \(+4.4\%\) ; NAB: \(+3.7\%\) ; WBC: \(+1.0\%\) ), based on APRA data.
For 2H25, mortgage growth is tracking roughly in line with our forecast of \(\sim 6\%\) at ANZ and NAB, but below our estimate of \(\sim 4\%\) at WBC.
Annualised growth in loans to non- financial businesses has held firm at \(\sim 10\%\) over the past 3 and 6 months.
Household deposits grew at an annualised rate of \(\sim 7.5\%\) over the past three months, with CBA leading among the majors and ANZ posting the weakest growth.

A robust outlook for loan growth: We believe the outlook for loan growth remains robust, supported by a combination of lower interest rates, improving consumer confidence, and a strong fiscal pulse. Australian mortgage growth has accelerated to \(\sim 6\%\) in the past year, with major banks such as ANZ, CBA, and NAB currently tracking broadly in line with system. At the same time, SME or business loan growth continues to meet or exceed our expectations. Given this momentum, we expect housing loan growth at the major banks to reach an average of \(\sim 5.5\%\) (refer Exhibit 2) and business loan growth to remain robust at \(\sim 7\%\) in FY26E.

Our view on the major banks: We believe a better operating environment, low earnings risk and healthy balance sheets will keep trading multiples above post- COVID averages. NAB (OW) is our preferred major bank, while WBC (UW) moves to our least preferred behind CBA (UW). For details, refer Aust Banks: Good Times, High Prices (27 Aug 2025).

Overweight (O). The stock's total return is expected to exceed the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.

Equal- weight (E). The stock's total return is expected to be in line with the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.

Not- Rated (NR). Currently the analyst does not have adequate conviction about the stock's total return relative to the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk- adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.

Underweight (U). The stock's total return is expected to be below the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk- adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.
Unless otherwise specified, the time frame for price targets included in Morgan Stanley Research is 12 to 18 months.
